@17081 = ~mana sorcerer~
@17082 = ~Mana Sorcerer~
@17083 = ~MANA SORCERER: Sorcerers are practitioners of magic who were born with the innate ability to cast spells. It is thought that the blood of some powerful creature flows through their veins; perhaps they are the spawn of the gods themselves, or even dragons walking in humanoid form. Regardless, the Sorcerer's magic is intuitive rather than logical. They know fewer spells than Mages, and acquire spells more slowly, but they can cast spells more often and have no need to select and prepare spells ahead of time.

Advantages:
- May cast arcane spells.
- Sorcerers do not scribe and memorize spells as Mages do. Instead, they learn a small number of spells at each level, and can cast any of those spells without memorization.
- Mana Sorcerers do not use "spell slots" of different levels. Instead, they have a single pool of Mana Points from which to draw when casting spells. Each spell cast will reduce the pool of Mana Points by an amount equal to the spell's level. Mana Points regenerate when the sorcerer rests.

Disadvantages:
- May not learn spells from scrolls.
~
@17085 = ~Change casting method~
@17087 = ~Restorative Meditation~
@17088 = ~Restorative Meditation: this ability allows a sorcerer to rest and meditate between combat encounters, recovering a portion of <PRO_HISHER> mana points.~
