This cantrip causes a small chunk of stone to fly from the caster's hands, doing 1d5 damage to the target.~
@6041   = ~Minor Spell Matrix~
@6042   = ~Minor Sequencer
(Invocation/Evocation)

Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows a wizard to store spells in a magical ability. This 'Spell Matrix' ability can store three spells of up to 4th level, to be released simultaneously. A wizard can only possess one spell matrix at a time, and the matrix may not be given to other characters. Once the spell matrix is used, the caster will gain the innate ability to create a new one.  (NOTE: upon casting this spell, it will be removed from the spell book, and thenceforth can be used from the Special Abilities button.)~
@6043   = ~Spell Sequencer~
@6044   = ~Spell Sequencer

Level: 7
Range: 0
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows a wizard to store spells in a magical ability. This 'Sequencer' ability can store three spells of up to 4th level, to be released simultaneously. A wizard can only possess one spell sequencer at a time, and the sequencer may not be given to other characters. Once the spell sequencer is used, the caster will gain the innate ability to create a new one.  (NOTE: upon casting this spell, it will be removed from the spell book, and thenceforth can be used from the Special Abilities button.)~
@6045   = ~Spell Trigger~
@6046   = ~Spell Trigger

Level: 8
Range: 0 
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster 
Saving Throw: None 

This spell allows a wizard to store spells in a magical ability. This 'Trigger' ability can store three spells of up to 6th level, to be released simultaneously. A wizard can only possess one spell trigger at a time, and the trigger may not be given to other characters. Once the spell trigger is used, the caster will gain the innate ability to create a new one.  (NOTE: upon casting this spell, it will be removed from the spell book, and thenceforth can be used from the Special Abilities button.)~
@6047   = ~Contingency~
@6048   = ~Contingency~
@6049   = ~Shadowstep~
@6050   = ~Shadowstep

The character steps into the Shadow Plane and may move for 7 seconds while others are frozen in time. The caster cannot attack or cast spells while in the Shadow Plane.~
@6051   = ~Parry Magic~
@6052   = ~Parry Magic

Level: 0
Range: 0
Duration: 15 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This ability causes the spells cast against the wizard to be deflected harmlessly away. It blocks a total of 2 spell levels, including spells cast from scrolls and innate spell-like abilities (but excludes area effects that are not aimed directly at the wizard). As long as the spell is cast directly at the wizard, it will be absorbed. If it tries to absorb a spell that over 2nd level, the spell will fail and the Deflection will be disrupted.~
@6053   = ~Spell Thrust~
@6054   = ~Spell Thrust

Level: 0
Range: 25 ft.
Duration: Instant
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast at a target creature, it will dispel a spell protections that has been erected, such as Minor spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, and Minor Spell Turning. The target's Magic Resistance does not affect this spell.  This ability can dispel protections of a level equal to the caster's level divided by three, rounded up. (But no matter how powerful the caster, a Spell Thrust will never break a Spell Trap.)~
@6055   = ~Bolt of Glory~
@6056   = ~Bolt of Glory
(Invocation/Evocation)

Sphere: Combat, Summoning
Level: 6
Range: 60 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

By casting this spell, the priest channels a bolt of divine energy against the target. No attack roll is needed. Creatures struck suffer varying damage, depending on their plane of origin:
 Creature Type                       Damage
 Prime Material Plane            6d6
 Elemental planes                 3d4
 Undead creatures                 8d6
 Fiends                               10d6
The divine bolt also has the power to dispel a wizard's spell protection (such as Spell Deflection or Spell Turning), though it is not powerful enough to disrupt a Spell Trap.~
@6057   = ~Secret Word~
@6058   = ~Secret Word

Level: 4
Range: 40 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast at a target creature, it will dispel one spell protection of 8th level or lower. Spells affected by this are Minor Spell Turning, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Spell Deflection, Spell Turning, and Spell Shield. 

Additionally, the target must save vs. spells or be deafened for 5 rounds, resulting in a 50% chance of miscast magic. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@6059   = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal~
@6060   = ~Ruby Ray of Reversal

Level: 7
Range: 40 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, it dispels one spell protection of any level affecting the target creature. The spells affected by Ruby Ray Of Reversal are Minor Spell Turning, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Minor Spell Deflection, Spell Turning, Spell Shield, Spell Deflection, and Spell Trap. This will always remove the highest-level spell protection affecting the target; if more than one same-level protection is active on the target simultaneously, one of them will be randomly chosen and dispelled.

Additionally, if the target fails a save vs. spells, the target will be blinded by the Ruby Ray for 3 rounds. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this spell.~
@6061   = ~Pierce Shield~
@6062   = ~Pierce Shield

Level: 8
Range: 40 ft.
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast, it launches a massive attack on an enemy wizard's spell defenses. The target's Magic Resistance will be lowered by 10% + 1% per level of the caster. Next, Pierce Shield will cancel one spell protection of any level. The list of spells that this includes: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Spell Turning, Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, Globe Of Invulnerability, Spell Turning, Spell Shield, and Spell Trap. Finally, Pierce Shield will cancel the target's magical combat protections, such as Shield or Stoneskin (but specific protections, such as Resistance to Fire, will remain).

Magic Resistance does not affect this spell, nor do any of the spell protections. The resistance remains lowered for 1 round per level of the caster. It cannot be dispelled.~
@6063   = ~Minor Spell Absorption~
@6064   = ~Minor Spell Absorption

Level: 4
Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed, making the caster recall a previously cast spell. For example, if hit by a Flame Arrow (a 3rd-level spell), the caster will get three spell levels back—e.g. one spell of up to 3rd level in power. It excludes area effects that are not centered directly upon the wizard. As long as the spell is cast directly at the wizard, it will be reflected back upon the caster. This spell will only affect up to 4th-level spells, but as long as there are levels remaining, a spell will be absorbed. For example, if there is only 1 level left and a 3rd-level spell is cast at the wizard, the spell will be absorbed and will exhaust the protection.

This spell will absorb and protect against a total of 5 spell levels of magic directed at the caster. It will not protect the caster from Dispel Magic, but will not be dispelled by Dispel Magic either.~
@6065   = ~Spell Absorption~
@6066   = ~Spell Absorption

Level: 6
Range: 0
Duration: 15 rounds
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed, making the caster recall a previously cast spell. For example, if hit by a Flame Arrow (a 3rd-level spell), the caster will get three spell levels back—e.g. one spell of up to 3rd level in power. It excludes area effects that are not centered directly upon the wizard. As long as the spell is cast directly at the wizard, it will be reflected back upon the caster. This spell will only affect up to 4th-level spells, but as long as there are levels remaining, a spell will be absorbed. For example, if there is only 1 level left and a 3rd-level spell is cast at the wizard, the spell will be absorbed and will exhaust the protection.

This spell will absorb and protect against a total of 10 spell levels of magic directed at the caster. It will not protect the caster from Dispel Magic, but will not be dispelled by Dispel Magic either.~
@6067   = ~Greater Spell Absorption~
@6068   = ~Greater Spell Absorption

Level: 7
Range: 0
Duration: 2 turns
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed, making the caster recall a previously cast spell.For example, if hit by a Flame Arrow (a 3rd-level spell), the caster will get three spell levels back—e.g. one spell of up to 3rd level in power. It excludes area effects that are not centered directly upon the wizard. As long as the spell is cast directly at the wizard, it will be reflected back upon the caster. This spell will only affect up to 4th-level spells, but as long as there are levels remaining, a spell will be absorbed. For example, if there is only 1 level left and a 3rd-level spell is cast at the wizard, the spell will be absorbed and will exhaust the protection.

This spell will absorb and protect against a total of 15 spell levels of magic directed at the caster. It will not protect the caster from Dispel Magic, but will not be dispelled by Dispel Magic either.~
@6069   = ~Spell Trap~
@6070   = ~Spell Trap

Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 20 turns
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: The caster 
Saving Throw: None 

This spell creates an incredibly powerful barrier of magical protection around the spellcaster. Every spell that hits the barrier is absorbed by the power of the spell trap—making the caster recall a previously cast spell. For example, if a wizard is protected by Spell Trap and is then hit by a Flame Arrow (3rd-level spell), the wizard will get three spell levels back—e.g. one spell up to 3rd level in power. 

The Spell Trap is remarkably stable, remaining in place for 4 hours unless dispelled or exhausted. It provides 30 levels of protection (i.e., ten Flame Arrows or five Fingers of Death). The spell trap can absorb any level of spell, from one to nine.~
@6071   = ~Protected by Spell Absorption~
@6072  = ~Magic Missile~
@6073  = ~Magic Missile
Level: 1
School: Evocation
Range: Long
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Use of the Magic Missile spell, one of the most popular first level spells, creates up to four missiles of magical energy that dart forth from the wizard's fingertip and unerringly strike their target, which must be a creature of some sort. Each missile inflicts 1d4+1 points of damage. The spell fires two missiles at 1st level, three at 5th level, and a maximum of four at 9th level.~
@6098   = ~Sorcerer~
@6099   = ~SORCERER: Sorcerers are practitioners of magic who were born with the innate ability to cast spells. It is thought that the blood of some powerful creature flows through their veins; perhaps they are the spawn of the gods themselves, or even dragons walking in humanoid form. Regardless, the Sorcerer's magic is intuitive rather than logical. They know fewer spells than Mages, and acquire spells more slowly, but they can cast spells more often and have no need to select and prepare spells ahead of time. Sorcerers cannot specialize in magic the way Mages do. Other than these differences, a Sorcerer is very similar to a Mage.

CLASS FEATURES:

– May not wear any armor.
– May only use the following weapons: dagger, quarterstaff, dart, sling.
– May only become Proficient (one slot) in any weapon class.
– May not place any slots in any fighting style.
– May cast arcane spells.
– May not scribe spells into their spellbooks as Mages do. Instead, Sorcerers learn a small number of spells at each level, which they can cast daily without memorization.
– Hit Die: d4~
@6111  = ~Grease
(Alteration)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Special

A Grease spell causes the surface of the ground to take on a slippery, greasy nature. Any creature entering the area or caught in it when the spell is cast must save vs. Spell at +2 or slip and slide, unable to move effectively. Those who successfully save can move, albeit slowly, for the rest of the round (but will need to save vs. Spell again the following round). Those who remain in the area are allowed a Saving Throw each round until they escape the area.~
@6112  = ~Protection From Evil
(Divination)

Level: 2
Range: Touch
Duration: 2 rounds/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When this spell is cast, it gives the protected creature a magical insight into the minds of any nearby creatures with evil intent. The slight foreknowledge that results causes all attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures to receive a penalty of -2 to each attack roll. Summoned demons and fiends are acutely affected by this spell; evil is woven into their very beings. Therefore, they are completely unable to target the protected creature.~
@6113  = ~Mirror Image (Illusion/Phantasm) 
Level: 3
Range: 0 
Duration: 3 rounds + 1 round/level 
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

When a mirror image spell is invoked, the spellcaster causes from two to eight exact duplicates of himself to come into being around him. These images do exactly what the wizard does. Since the spell causes a blurring and slight distortion when it is cast, it is impossible for opponents to be certain which are the illusions and which is the actual wizard. When an image is struck by a melee or missile attack, magical or otherwise, it disappears, but any other existing images remain intact until they are struck.  However, it is important to note that this will not protect the caster against every attack as it is possible for an enemy to choose the real caster amongst all the images.~
@6114  = ~Glitterdust
(Illusion)

Level: 2
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 30 ft.
Saving Throw: Neg.

This spell was created by an Invoker wizard who was convinced that he was being stalked by assassins with the ability to become invisible. Unfortunately, he had no skill with Divination spells. This spell showers glittering golden particles in the area of effect. Enemies must roll a successful Saving Throw vs. Spell or be blinded (-4 penalty to attack rolls and Armor Class) for 4 rounds. In addition, all enemies who fail their Saving Throw are covered by the dust, which cannot be removed and continues to sparkle until it fades, thus revealing invisible creatures. The dust fades in 4 rounds.~
@6115  = ~Luck
(Divination)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

The recipient of this gains a very slight, instinctive insight into the immediate future. The result is that the subject appears to be lucky in every regard for the next 3 rounds, receiving a 5% bonus to all actions. This includes Saving Throws, to-hit rolls, damage, thieving skills, etc.~
@6116  = ~Flame Arrow
(Alteration)

Level: 3
Range: 60 ft.
Duration: 1 round
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: 1/2

This spell begins with one or more common arrows or bolts, superheats them, and then hurls fiery bolts at opponents at very high speed. Each bolt inflicts 1d6 points of piercing damage plus 4d6 points of fire damage. Only half of the fire damage is inflicted if the creature struck saves vs. Spell. The caster receives one bolt every 5 levels beyond the 5th (2 bolts at 10th level, 3 at 15th level, etc.). All of the bolts will streak toward the target of the spell.~
@6117  = ~Greater Malison
(Enchantment/Charm)

Level: 4
Range: 50 ft.
Duration: 2 rounds/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

The spell grants the caster the ability to understand and subtly manipulate the flow of time, making any following spells more likely to be successful and effective. The practical result is to adversely affect all enemy Saving Throws. The effect is applied to all hostile creatures within the area of effect, who make all saving throws at a penalty of -4.~
@6118  = ~Shadow Stalker
(Illusion/Phamtasm)

Level: 6
Range: 120 ft.
Duration: 9 hours
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a double of the caster formed from pure shadow, and imparts upon it some degree of form and autonomy. Blurry and shapeless, this entity will fight on the caster's behalf and remain in relatively stable form for up to 9 hours (unless it meets a violent demise).~
@6119  = ~Mordenkainen's Sword
(Enchantment/Charm)

Level: 7
Range: 0
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

Upon casting this spell, the wizard temporarily imbues a normal blade with magical power and a will of its own. The sword will float in the air completely under the caster's control. (This does not prevent the caster from doing any other actions during the spell's duration.) The sword acts as a +4 weapon in all respects and deals 5d4 points of damage upon hitting a target.~
@6120  = ~Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting
(Necromancy) 

Level: 8
Range: Visual range of the caster 
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: 1/2

This spell creates violent whorls of magical energy within the area of effect which do grievous harm to all enemies, inflicting 1d8 damage per level of the caster. Affected creatures are allowed a Saving Throw vs. Spell for half damage. This spell is especially devastating to water elementals and plant creatures, who receive a penalty of -2 to their Saving Throws.~
@6121  = ~Black Blade of Disaster
(Enchantment/Charm) 

Level: 8
Range: 0
Duration: 18 rounds
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

This spell imposes a black, magical planar rift over the blade of a normal weapon. The caster becomes a Grand Master in the use of the weapon. It acts as a +5 weapon and deals 2-24 damage to its victims. Every time it hits a target, the victim must make a Save vs. Death at +4 or be disintegrated. There is also a 10% chance with every hit that the sword drains 4 levels from the target and heals the wielder 20 Hit Points.~
@6122  = ~Weird
(Illusion/Phantasm) 

Level: 9
Range: Visual range of the caster 
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

This spell creates phantasmal visions of unimaginable horror in the mind of all enemies in the area of effect. The spell is risky because such intense and unreal illusions may be disbelieved (subjects may avoid the effects if they make a saving throw vs. death). But affected creatures who fail their save are so drastically affected that they die instantly.~
@6123  = ~Wizard Eye
(Necromancy)

Level: 4
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

