@7126  = ~When activated, the wand will fire two missiles of magical energy that dart forth and unerringly strike the target. This includes enemy creatures in a melee. The target creature must be seen or otherwise detected to be hit, however, so near-total concealment, such as that offered by arrow slits, can render the wand ineffective. Each missile will inflict 1d4+1 points of damage.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
  2 magic missiles will strike the target
  Damage: 1d4+1 magic each
  Range: 100 ft.
  Area of Effect: 1 creature

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1
~
@7151  = ~Shocking Grasp~
@7152  = ~Shocking Grasp
(Alteration)

Level: 1
Range: Touch
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

When the wizard touches a creature while this spell is in effect, an electrical charge will deal 1d8 points of damage, plus 1 additional point per two levels of the caster (to a maximum of 1d8+5 points of damage, at 10th level.) In addition, the grasp itself does 1d2 fist damage (Strength bonuses apply). The wizard only has one charge, and once an opponent has been touched, the spell's energies have been used. If the wizard misses, the spell is wasted. The wizard has 1 round per level to touch the target creature.
~
@7154  = ~Shocking Grasp

Level: 1
School: Evocation
Range: Personal
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

When the wizard touches a creature while this spell is in effect, an electrical charge will deal 2d4 points of damage and stun the target for 1 round. If the target makes a successful saving throw vs. spell, he is not stunned. For every two extra experience levels of the caster, the creature will suffer an additional points of damage and roll their saving throw at an increased -1 penalty (to a maximum of 2d4+4 damage and a -4 saving throw penalty, at 9th level). The spell expires once the caster makes a successful melee attack or after 1 turn has passed. The wizard gains a +4 bonus to hit the target.
~
@7161  = ~Drowse~
@7162  = ~Drowse
(Enchantment/Charm)

Level: 1
Range: 60 ft.
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 1 
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

When a wizard casts this spell, <PRO_HESHE> causes slumber to come upon one enemy (other than undead and certain other creatures specifically excluded from the spell's effects). The creature must make a saving throw vs. Spells or fall asleep. Attacks against sleeping opponents never miss.

If the sleeping creature takes damage, <PRO_HESHE> will slowly wake up over the course of 1 round. Additionally, once a creature has been put to sleep by this spell, that being cannot be affected by another casting of the spell for 8 hours.
~
@7163  = ~Sleep~
@7164  = ~Sleep
(Enchantment/Charm)

Level: 2
Range: 60 ft.
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 1 
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

When a wizard casts this spell, <PRO_HESHE> causes a comatose slumber to come upon one or more enemies within a 30-ft. radius (other than undead and certain other creatures specifically excluded from the spell's effects). Creatures in the area of effect must make a saving throw vs. Spells with a -3 penalty or fall asleep. Monsters with 5 Hit Dice or more are unaffected. Attacks against sleeping opponents never miss.

If a sleeping creature takes damage, they will slowly wake up over the course of 1 round. Additionally, once a creature has been put to sleep by this spell, that being cannot be affected by another casting of the spell for 8 hours.
~
@7171 = ~Frost Fingers~
@7172 = ~Frost Fingers
(Invocation)

Level: 1
Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: none

When this spell is cast, a jet of chilling frost shoots from the caster's fingertips, in jets of 5 ft. length in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees in front of the caster. Any creature in the area receives 1d6 points of cold damage, plus 1 additional point for each three levels of the caster (to a maximum of 1d6+6 damage).
~
@7181  = ~Chromatic Orb~
@7182  = ~Chromatic Orb
(Evocation)

Level: 1
Range: 90 ft.
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

This spell causes a colorful sphere to appear in the caster's hand. When thrown, the sphere heads unerringly to its target. The effect the orb varies. Each orb will do damage to the target against which there is no save, and can trigger a secondary effect against which the target must save vs. Spell with a +2 bonus:
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and blinds the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and inflicts pain (-1 penalty to Strength, Dexterity, AC, and THAC0) upon the target.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and stuns the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and causes weakness (-4 penalty to THAC0) in the target for 5 rounds.
 20% chance: 1d4 damage and panics the target for 2 rounds.
~
@7191  = ~Larloch's Minor Drain~
@7192  = ~Larloch's Minor Drain 
(Necromancy)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

With this spell, the wizard drains the life force from a target and adds it to <PRO_HISHER> own. The target creature suffers 2d3 damage (save vs. Death for half damage), while the caster gains 4 hit points. If the caster goes over <PRO_HISHER> maximum hit point total with this spell, <PRO_HESHE> loses any extra hit points after 1 turn.

A caster may only benefit from the extra hit points provided by this spell once per turn, regardless how many victims are drained, or how quickly.
~
@7241  = ~Wild Surge~
@7242  = ~Wild Surge
(Invocation/Evocation)

Level: 1
Range: Special
Duration: Special
Casting Time: Special
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

This is less a spell than a release of pure wild energy. Magic energy surrounds wild mages and courses through them. This effect is what happens if a wild mage loses control and allows such energy to be unleashed. There is no spell, no intended form the magic takes; only pure, random, magical manifestation.

Wild mages may release this energy at any time, as often as they like; but most spend their careers learning how to prevent it happening, rather than how to make it happen.
~
@7251  = ~Spook~
@7252  = ~Spook
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Level: 1
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Neg.

A Spook spell enables the wizard to play upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the caster as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful Saving Throw vs. Spell, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wizard as possible. The creature suffers a Saving Throw penalty of -1 every 2 levels of the caster, up to a maximum of -6 at 12th level. Although the caster does not actually pursue the fleeing creature, a phantasm from its own mind does. Undead are completely unaffected.

Anyone who has been the target of this spell - whether they make their saving throw or not - will be suspicious for a time, and cannot be affected by it for 8 hours. 
~

@7101  = ~Identify~
@7102  = ~Identify

Level: 1
School: Divination
Range: Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None 

The caster of this spell gains a temporary insight into the history and nature of magical objects. This translates into a temporary Lore bonus of 20 points, plus an additional 20 points for each five levels of experience the caster has attained. If the resulting score is high enough, the spell can identify the name, nature, and function of any magical items in the caster's possession.
~
@7103  = ~Identify~
@7104  = ~Identify

Level: 1
School: Divination
Range: 0
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: None 

When this spell is cast, name and enchantments (including curses) of one item or weapon subsequently touched by the caster are revealed without fail. This gives the caster insight into the history, nature, enchantments, and use of the item. Many unidentified items can still be used, but at great risk.

At 5th, 9th, and 13th level, the number of items that can be identified by this spell increases by 1 (to a maximum of 4 items at 13th level).
~
@8002  = ~Find Familiar
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Level: 1
Range: n/a
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 familiar
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the caster to summon a familiar to act as <PRO_HISHER> aide and companion. Familiars are typically small creatures. A creature acting as a familiar can benefit a wizard, conveying its sensory powers to its master, conversing with <PRO_HIMHER>, and serving as a guard, scout, or spy. A wizard can have only one familiar at a time, and <PRO_HESHE> has no control over what sort of creature answers the summoning, if any come at all.

(Note: This spell may only be cast by the protagonist.)

A familiar is more intelligent than others of its type. Its bond with the wizard confers upon it an exceptionally long life, allows it to regenerate 1 hit point per round, and to resist petrification and level drain effects. The caster receives half the familiar's total Hit Points (rounded down) as bonus Hit Points. However, the caster must take care to treat <PRO_HISHER> familiar well, for if the familiar should die, the caster loses the bonus Hit Points and the familiar's Hit Points again as damage. Also when a familiar dies, the caster loses 1 point of Constitution PERMANENTLY.

At 1st level, all familiars share the following characteristics: 9 hit points, AC 4, thac0 17, saving throws 16, 25% magic and damage resistance, immunity to level drain and petrification. At certain experience thresholds - 5,000 / 50,000 / 150,000 / 450,000 / 1,250,000 / 2,500,000 / 4,000,000 - the familiar's hit points, AC, thac0 and saving throws will improve.

Here is a list of the familiars that the player may choose:

Pseudo Dragon
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage; save or be Slowed for 2 rounds
- Special Abilities: can cast Blur and Cure Light Wounds, and use a Color Spray breath weapon, once every 3 turns.
- Special Benefit: the pseudodragon's summoner regenerates 1 hit point per round.

Ferret
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage
- Special Abilities: has 80% Pick Pockets score. Can emit a small aura of Nauseating Stench once per turn. For five round, enemies near the ferret must save or suffer 2-point penalties to hit and AC and a 30% chance of casting failure.
- Special Benefit: the ferret's summoner has a +1 bonus to Constitution.

Rabbit
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage
- Special Abilities: has 80% Detect Traps score. Can burrow into the ground to escape danger - similar to the Shadowstep ability - once per turn.
- Special Benefit: the rabbit's summoner is immune to Slow effects.

Cat
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage
- Special Abilities: has 99% in Move Silently/Hide in Shadows, and is Nondetectable (as the spell) to magic divinations.
- Special Benefit: the cat's summoner has a +1 bonus to Dexterity.

Spider
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage; save or take 3 poison damage over 1 round
- Special Abilities: can cast a single-target Web, which can tangle the target for 3 rounds, once per 5 rounds.
- Special Benefit: the spider's summoner has an extra chance to resist being affected by poisons.

Rat
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage; save or be diseased for 3 rounds, with reduced Strength and a 30% chance of casting failure
- Special Abilities: can summon a cohort of 1d6 more rats to defend it, once per 3 turns.
- Special Benefit: the rat's summoner has a +1 bonus to Intelligence.
~
