@8011  = ~Pseudodragon~
@8012  = ~Pseudodragon: this is a tiny, distant relative of full dragons. The pseudodragon can cast Cure Light Wounds, and Blur, and use a colorful 'breath weapon' that mimics the Color Spray spell, once every 3 turns. (At high levels, the Blur improves to a full Improved Invisibility effect.) They can attack twice per round and while their claws are small, they deliver a mild intoxicant which can render the target drowsy and clumsy (mimicking the effects of a Slow spell, for two rounds). 

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner regenerates 1 hit point per round.

As pseudodragons can fly, they are impervious to the effects of Grease, Entangle, Web, and similar spells. As with all familiars, their magical connection to the life force of their master renders them immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
@8013  = ~Pseudodragon~
@8014  = ~Pseudodragon: pseudodragons are quite intelligent. While small, they are  quick and fairly well-armored. They do not do much damage in combat, but their magical claws are able to render some enemies unconscious. It is also quite resistant to magical spells.

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner will slowly regenerate health.

As with all familiars, its magical connection to the life force of its master renders it immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
@8015  = ~Dog~
@8016  = ~Dog: ...~
@8017  = ~Ferret~
@8018  = ~Ferret: these animals are clever and mischievous, and while cute, they can occasionally carry a noxious stench. In combat they can attack twice per round, and they can emit a small-range nauseating aura which can cause nearby enemies to gag and retch, resulting in 2-point penalties to hit and armor class, and a 30% chance of spell failure.

Ferrets are also sneaky, and can make effective pickpockets on behalf of their masters.  

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner benefits from a +1 bonus to Constitution.

As with all familiars, its magical connection to the life force of its master renders it immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
@8019  = ~Rabbit~
@8020  = ~Rabbit: while the rabbit is not an impressive combatant, it is exceedingly skilled at avoiding damage. Rabbits have 25% resistance to elemental attacks, and once per turn they can burrow into the ground and move unheeded to a safe area (in practice this resembles the ShadowStep ability of Shadowdancers). Rabbits also have an acute sense of imending danger, and can quite effectively use their sensitive noses and ears to sniff out nearby traps.

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner is immune to Slow spells and similar effects.

As with all familiars, its magical connection to the life force of its master renders it immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
@8021  = ~Cat~
@8022  = ~Cat: a black cat is a very traditional familiar for wizards, and is quite useful as a scout. They can move unseen as well as any master thief; and they may escape notice even in the face of spells that expose invisible creatures (though creatures with the natural ability to see hidden and invisible beings can still spot a cat).

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner benefits from a +1 bonus to Dexterity.

As with all familiars, its magical connection to the life force of its master renders it immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
@8023  = ~Imp~
@8024  = ~Imp: ~
@8025  = ~Spider~
@8026  = ~Spider: a spider can make a useful, if somewhat creepy-crawly, familiar for a wizard with no aversion to arachnids. They are effective in combat, especially against spellcasters, as they inject victims with a poison that can inflict 3 extra points of damage over 6 seconds. This particular variety of large spiders has the ability to, once every 5 rounds, spit a sticky mess of webbing at an enemy, who may be held fast in it for 3 rounds on a failed saving throw.

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner has an extra chance to save to avoid spells or effects that cause poison damage.

Spiders cannot be held fast by Web spells or similar effects. As with all familiars, its magical connection to the life force of its master renders it immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
